OL,3,CResidents in Somerset to face 7.5%
OL,4,Ccouncil tax hike due to #66m deficit
OL,6,FResidents in Somerset are set to see
OL,7,Ftheir council tax bills rise by 7.5%
OL,8,Ffrom April, as the government has
OL,9,Fapproved plans to allow the unusually
OL,10,Flarge hike.
OL,12,FLocal authorities such as Somerset
OL,13,FCouncil are usually only allowed to
OL,14,Fraise council tax by a maximum of
OL,15,Faround 5%.
OL,17,FBut many councils are facing
OL,18,Fthemselves in dire financial positions
OL,19,Fand all must legally balance their
OL,20,Fbudgets before the beginning of the
OL,21,Fnew financial year in the spring.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
